## Key Design Decisions

### Radial Gradients over Konva.Filters.Blur
The existing `Nebula` component (used in DeepSpaceLayer) achieves soft, gaseous clouds using `fillRadialGradient` ‚Äî no bitmap blur needed. Konva.Filters.Blur requires `node.cache()` + CPU-based box blur on every redraw, which is extremely expensive for large shapes. We'll follow the existing pattern: canvas `createRadialGradient()` that fades to transparent, producing the same visual effect with hardware acceleration.

### Per-cloud rotation instead of layer rotation
Rotating the entire layer would drift nebulae away from their galaxy clusters. Instead, each cloud rotates individually around its own center, keeping the spatial correlation intact while still giving the "breathing" feel.

### Batch rendering via single Shape
Consistent with DeepSpaceLayer and MidGalaxyLayer ‚Äî all nebula clouds drawn in one `Shape` `sceneFunc` call instead of individual Konva nodes. This avoids creating N Konva Circle objects and keeps the scene graph lightweight.

